Error code (optional)\n75: - [ ] Define `JWTClaims` struct\n76:   - [ ] `SessionID string`\n77:   - [ ] `jwt.RegisteredClaims`\n78: - [ ] Add JSON tags for all struct fields\n79: - [ ] Create `types_test.go` with struct validation tests\n80:   - [ ] `TestSandboxInfoJSONSerialization`\n81:   - [ ] `TestErrorResponseJSONSerialization`\n82:   - [ ] `TestSandboxEntryPointValidation`\n83: \n84: **Verification**: Run `go test ./pkg/router -run TestTypes` and verify JSON serialization works correctly\n85: \n86: ---\n87: \n88: ### Task 4: Implement JWT manager for authentication\n89: - [ ] Create `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n90: - [ ] Define `JWTManager` struct\n91:   - [ ] `privateKey *rsa.PrivateKey`\n92:   - [ ] `publicKey *rsa.PublicKey`\n93:   - [ ] `clientset kubernetes.Interface`\n94:   - [ ] `namespace string`\n95: - [ ] Implement `NewJWTManager()` constructor function\n96: - [ ] Implement `GenerateToken()` method\n97:   - [ ] Create JWT claims with session ID\n98:   - [ ] Set token expiration (5 minutes)\n99:   - [ ] Sign token with RSA private key\n100:   - [ ] Return signed token string\n101: - [ ] Implement `ValidateToken()` method\n102:   - [ ] Parse and verify token signature\n103:   - [ ] Extract session ID from claims\n104:   - [ ] Validate token expiration\n105:   - [ ] Return session ID or error\n106: - [ ] Implement `generateRSAKeyPair()` private method\n107:   - [ ] Generate 2048-bit RSA key pair\n108:   - [ ] Return private and public keys\n109: - [ ] Implement `storeOrLoadJWTKeySecret()` method\n110:   - [ ] Check for existing Kubernetes secret\n111:   - [ ] Load keys from secret if exists\n112:   - [ ] Generate and store new keys if not exists\n113: - [ ] Implement `storeJWTKeySecret()` private method\n114:   - [ ] Create/update Kubernetes secret\n115:   - [ ] Store RSA keys as base64-encoded values\n116: - [ ] Create `jwt_test.go` with comprehensive tests\n117:   - [ ] `TestGenerateToken`\n118:   - [ ] `TestValidateToken`\n119:   - [ ] `TestTokenExpiration`\