{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775851816642,"sessionID":"ses_286fd0597ffeUvSKPGO0JQDwqU","part":{"id":"prt_d790446a0001z9IORinx8E3WDf","messageID":"msg_d790386ea0010OQ8Hb0m19coi2","sessionID":"ses_286fd0597ffeUvSKPGO0JQDwqU","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-d989877c8c704a019a5b8408edded41f","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-011 — Router JWT 认证与签发 Implementation Tasks\n\n**Module**: `pkg/router`\n**Language**: Go\n**Size**: M\n**Design Stage**: ST-3 Completed\n\n## Task Breakdown\n\n### Task 1: Fix isNotFoundError implementation in jwt.go\n- [ ] Update `isNotFoundError()` function in `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n- [ ] Import `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/api/errors` package\n- [ ] Check error using `errors.IsNotFound(err)` instead of hardcoded false\n- [ ] Add test case for Secret not found scenario\n- [ ] Add test case for other Kubernetes API errors\n\n**Verification**: Run `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTSecretNotFound` to verify error detection works correctly\n\n---\n\n### Task 2: Implement JWT authentication middleware\n- [ ] Create `pkg/router/jwt_middleware.go` file\n- [ ] Implement `jwtAuthMiddleware()` function accepting *JWTManager parameter\n- [ ] Extract Authorization header from request\n- [ ] Validate Bearer scheme in Authorization header\n- [ ] Call JWTManager.ValidateToken() with extracted token\n- [ ] Store session_id in Gin context on successful validation\n- [ ] Return 401 Unauthorized with structured error on validation failure\n- [ ] Add correlation ID logging for authentication failures\n- [ ] Handle missing Authorization header with 401 Unauthorized\n- [ ] Handle invalid token format with 401 Unauthorized\n- [ ] Handle expired tokens with appropriate error message\n\n**Verification**: Run `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTMiddleware` to verify middleware behavior\n\n---\n\n### Task 3: Add JWT-specific error definitions\n- [ ] Update `pkg/router/errors.go`\n- [ ] Define JWT error constants:\n  - [ ] `ErrJWTValidationFailed` = \"JWT_VALIDATION_FAILED\"\n  - [ ] `ErrJWTTokenExpired` = \"JWT_TOKEN_EXPIRED\"\n  - [ ] `ErrJWTTokenInvalid` = \"JWT_TOKEN_INVALID\"\n  - [ ] `ErrJWTTokenMissing` = \"JWT_TOKEN_MISSING\"\n  - [ ] `ErrJWTSigningFailed` = \"JWT_SIGNING_FAILED\"\n- [ ] Define `JWTValidationError` struct implementing HTTPError interface\n- [ ] Implement Error() method returning detailed but safe error message\n- [ ] Implement HTTPStatusCode() method returning 401\n- [ ] Implement ErrorCode() method returning appropriate error code\n- [ ] Add unit tests for each JWT error type\n\n**Verification**: Run `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTErrors` to verify error definitions\n\n---\n\n### Task 4: Update session creation to include JWT token generation\n- [ ] Update `pkg/router/handlers.go` session creation handlers\n- [ ] Add JWT token generation to AgentRuntime session creation response\n- [ ] Add JWT token generation to CodeInterpreter session creation response\n- [ ] Update response structures to include `token` field\n- [ ] Ensure session ID matches between response and JWT claims\n- [ ] Handle JWT generation failures gracefully\n- [ ] Add logging for successful token generation\n- [ ] Add logging for token generation failures\n\n**Verification**: Run `go test ./pkg/router -run TestSessionCreationWithToken` to verify token generation\n\n---\n\n### Task 5: Create comprehensive JWT unit tests\n- [ ] Create `pkg/router/jwt_test.go` file\n- [ ] Implement `TestNewJWTManager_Success` test\n- [ ] Implement `TestNewJWTManager_NilClientset` test\n- [ ] Implement `TestNewJWTManager_DefaultNamespace` test\n- [ ] Implement `TestGenerateToken_Success` test\n- [ [ ] Implement `TestGenerateToken_NoPrivateKey` test\n- [ ] Implement `TestValidateToken_Success` test\n- [ ] Implement `TestValidateToken_ExpiredToken` test\n- [ ] Implement `TestValidateToken_InvalidSignature` test\n- [ ] Implement `TestValidateToken_NoPublicKey` test\n- [ ] Implement `TestGenerateRSAKeyPair` test\n- [ ] Implement `TestStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret_CreateNew` test (mock Kubernetes)\n- [ ] Implement `TestStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret_LoadExisting` test (mock Kubernetes)\n- [ ] Implement `TestLoadKeysFromSecret_MissingPrivateKey` test\n- [ ] Implement `TestLoadKeysFromSecret_MissingPublicKey` test\n- [ ] Implement `TestParsePrivateKeyPEM_Success` test\n- [ ] Implement `TestParsePrivateKeyPEM_InvalidFormat` test\n- [ ] Implement `TestParsePublicKeyPEM_Success` test\n- [ ] Implement `TestParsePublicKeyPEM_InvalidFormat` test\n- [ ] Implement `TestJWTClaimsSerialization` test\n\n**Verification**: Run `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWT` to verify all JWT unit tests pass\n\n---\n\n### Task 6: Create JWT middleware tests\n- [ ] Implement `TestJWTAuthMiddleware_ValidToken` test\n- [ ] Implement `TestJWTAuthMiddleware_MissingToken` test\n- [ ] Implement `TestJWTAuthMiddleware_InvalidToken` test\n- [ ] Implement `TestJWTAuthMiddleware_ExpiredToken` test\n- [ ] Implement `TestJWTAuthMiddleware_WrongScheme` test\n- [ ] Implement `TestJWTAuthMiddleware_SessionIDInContext` test\n- [ ] Implement `TestJWTAuthMiddleware_ErrorResponseFormat` test\n- [ ] Test correlation ID logging on authentication failures\n\n**Verification**: Run `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTMiddleware` to verify middleware tests pass\n\n---\n\n### Task 7: Create JWT middleware tests with table-driven approach\n- [ ] Implement table-driven test for middleware scenarios\n- [ ] Test case: Valid Bearer token → Success\n- [ ] Test case: Missing Authorization header → 401\n- [ ] Test case: Empty Authorization header → 401\n- [ ] Test case: Authorization header without \"Bearer\" → 401\n- [ ] Test case: Malformed token string → 401\n- [ ] Test case: Expired token → 401 with expiration error\n- [ ] Test case: Invalid signature → 401 with validation error\n- [ ] Test case: Valid token with session_id → Context set\n\n**Verification**: Run `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTMiddlewareTableDriven` to verify all scenarios\n\n---\n\n### Task 8: Implement JWT-related logging enhancements\n- [ ] Update `pkg/router/jwt.go` logging statements\n- [ ] Add Info level log when keys are loaded from Secret\n- [ ] Add Info level log when keys are stored in Secret\n- [ ] Add Warning level log when Secret access fails and fallback occurs\n- [ ] Add Error level log when key generation fails\n- [ ] Update middleware logging for authentication failures\n- [ ] Add correlation ID to all JWT-related log entries\n- [ ] Ensure no sensitive information (private keys) is logged\n\n**Verification**: Review log output during test runs to verify appropriate logging levels and messages\n\n---\n\n### Task 9: Create JWT performance benchmarks\n- [ ] Create benchmark functions in `pkg/router/jwt_test.go`\n- [ ] Implement `BenchmarkGenerateToken` to measure token generation speed\n- [ ] Implement `BenchmarkValidateToken` to measure token validation speed\n- [ ] Implement `BenchmarkGenerateRSAKeyPair` to measure key generation speed\n- [ ] Implement `BenchmarkConcurrentTokenGeneration` to test concurrent operations\n- [ ] Implement `BenchmarkConcurrentTokenValidation` to test concurrent operations\n- [ ] Target: P99 latency for GenerateToken < 10ms\n- [ ] Target: P99 latency for ValidateToken < 5ms\n\n**Verification**: Run `go test ./pkg/router -bench=BenchmarkJWT -benchmem` to verify performance targets\n\n---\n\n### Task 10: Create JWT security tests\n- [ ] Create `pkg/router/jwt_security_test.go`\n- [ ] Implement `TestSecurity_AlgorithmConfusionAttack` test\n- [ ] Implement `TestSecurity_NoneAlgorithmAttack` test\n- [ ] Implement `TestSecurity_TokenTampering` test\n- [ ] Implement `TestSecurity_ReplayAttack` test\n- [ ] Implement `TestSecurity_LongTokenAttack` test\n- [ ] Implement `TestSecurity_InvalidBase64Token` test\n- [ ] Implement `TestSecurity_MissingRequiredClaims` test\n- [ ] Test that middleware prevents algorithm confusion\n- [ ] Test that tokens with \"none\" algorithm are rejected\n\n**Verification**: Run `go test ./pkg/ro